What's Changed
Add numerous missing
@preconcurrency
attributes by
@gwynne
in
#3074
It has become standard practice to add
@Sendable
to
@escaping
closures passed as method parameters to improve Concurrency correctness. However, when this is done for pre-existing
public
methods that are
not
async
, the result is source incompatibility for some users, as mutable values captured by such closures will cause unexpected build errors. The correct way to suppress this behavior is to mark such methods with the
@preconcurrency
attribute, signaling to the compiler that users may not yet expect the additional restrictions of
@Sendable
to apply without sacrificing correctness for Concurrency-ready code. Unfortunately, Vapor recently added
@Sendable
annotations to many of its APIs without also adding the
@preconcurrency
annotation; this update addresses that oversight.
This patch was released by
@gwynne
